ENTRY       EC 1.2.1.81                 Enzyme
NAME        sulfoacetaldehyde dehydrogenase (acylating);
            SauS
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     2-sulfoacetaldehyde:NADP+ oxidoreductase (CoA-acetylating)
REACTION    2-sulfoacetaldehyde + CoA + NADP+ = sulfoacetyl-CoA + NADPH + H+ [RN:R09557]
ALL_REAC    R09557
SUBSTRATE   2-sulfoacetaldehyde [CPD:C00593];
            CoA [CPD:C00010];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     sulfoacetyl-CoA [CPD:C19685];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005];
            H+ [CPD:C00080]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in degradation of sulfoacetate. In this pathway the reaction is catalysed in the reverse direction. The enzyme is specific for sulfoacetaldehyde and NADP+.
